snippet: That tops the roughly $3.2 million that Senator Scott P. Brown of Massachusetts raised during the same period for what promises to be one of the costliest races in the country.
abstract: That tops the roughly $3.2 million that Senator Scott P. Brown of Massachusetts raised during the same period for what promises to be one of the costliest races in the country.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON - Elizabeth Warren, the Harvard professor seeking the Democratic nomination to challenge Senator Scott P. Brown of Massachusetts in November, announced Wednesday that she had raised $5.7 million in the last three months of 2011.

headline.main: Warren Raised $5.7 Million for Senate Bid
